node.text:
Veering away from the conventions of traditional yacht design led Sanlorenzo to discover an alternative layout that optimises the utilisation of interior spaces and the connection of life onboard to the sea. This was achieved by opting for an asymmetrical design, the namesake feature of the 37m SL120 Asymmetric. This series, of which two are already on the water and another five are currently in-build, eliminates the starboard side deck in order to maximise interior living space through the addition of a dining room to starboard and a living area that opens onto a balcony to port. In addition to this central feature, the SL120A has ample deck space including a large beach club situated on the lower deck aft, which opens from three sides to further emphasise the connection to the sea.
Video courtesy of @sanlorenzoyacht

node.text: Ferretti Yachts’ flagship series, the 30-metre Ferretti Yachts 1000, is the Italian shipbuilder’s largest and most impressive model to date. Filippo Salvetti penned her sleek exterior lines and Ferretti Yachts has completed her naval architecture in house. In addition to her generous interior volume of 170 GT, the Ferretti Yachts 1000 has ample deck space including her spacious upper deck and, arguably most impressive feature, her 40 square-metre beach club. Situated at the superyacht’s transom, guests can make use of her hydraulically-operated submersible platform. The Ferretti Yachts 1000 is equipped with twin MTU engines, which allow her to reach a notable top speed of 28 knots. The first unit of the project was launched this March and is expected to be delivered later this year, with six additional units currently in build.

The Maiora 30 Convertible will make her world debut at this year’s Cannes Yachting Festival, which will take place from the 7th through the 12th of September. At the heart of the Maiora-designed, 30.5-metre motor yacht is her fully openable sky lounge. Whether it is closed to provide maximum comfort and privacy or opened to create an unparalleled connection to the sea, this standout design feature serves to optimise life on the water.

node.text:
SilverYachts is currently busy with the construction of the second hull of the 85-metre Silver Loft model. Known under the project name Silver World Explorer, she will feature many of the same elements as her sistership, the famed superyacht Bold. According to SilverYachts’ founder Guido Krass, “It is not just the same platform, it is the same identical boat.” Silver World Explorer will have the same proven world-cruising capacity, host an array of tenders and toys and much more. The in-build superyacht is currently in search of an owner ahead of her delivery, which is expected during the second quarter of 2022.
Video by @silveryachts
